1 (4) For the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2027 2025, the department shall adjust the room and
2 board payment levels as provided in this section on July 1, 2027, and on January 1, 2028 2026.
3
4 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Direction to department of public health and human services. The
5 legislature directs the department of public health and human services to apply for a state plan amendment no
6 later than January 1, 2028 2026, to make assisted living facility services currently covered under the big sky
7 waiver a service covered under the community first choice option available under the medicaid program.
8
9 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Reporting requirements -- big sky waiver and community first
10 choice programs. (1) Each quarter of the 2029 2027 biennium, the department of public health and human
11 services shall report the following information for the preceding quarter to the health and human services
12 interim budget committee provided for in 5-12-501:
13 (a) the average number of people served each month through the big sky waiver and the
14 community first choice option administered by the division overseeing long-term care services;
15 (b) the average number of people on the waiting list for the big sky waiver each month;
16 (c) any changes in the number of providers participating in the community first choice option;
17 (d) the average per-capita expenditures in the big sky waiver and the community first choice
18 option; and
19 (e) the average utilization rate of individual service plan allotments in the community first choice
20 option.
21 (2) The reports must be provided in electronic format and presented to the committee in person.
22
23 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
24 integral part of Title 53, chapter 6, and the provisions of Title 53, chapter 6, apply to [section 1].
25
26 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2027 2025.
27 - END -
